==English==
===Noun===
'''flare''' ([[flares]])

# A [[brightly]] burning [[light]] used to attract attention in an [[emergency]], or to [[illuminate]] an area.
# A widening of the lower legs of [[trousers]] and [[jeans]].
# ([[aircraft]]) the [[transition]] from [[downward]] [[flight]] to [[level]] flight just before landing.
#{{baseball}} A low [[fly ball]] that is hit in the region between the [[infielder]]s and the [[outfielder]]s
#: ''Jones hits a little ''flare'' to left that falls for a ''single''.''

===Intransitive Verb===
'''to flare'''

# to [[blaze]] brightly
# to [[burn]] unsteadily
# to burst out suddenly, as in anger (often with ''up'' or ''out'')

===Transitive Verb===
'''to make flare'''

===Related terms===
*[[flare up]]
*[[lens flare]]
*[[parachute flare]]

